92
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:41,010
That's not the problem.

93
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:43,940
We just seem to be
unbalanced somehow.

94
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:47,310
But you're the one who
I'd make a good weapon.

95
00:05:47,310 --> 00:05:50,520
At this rate,we won't
even reach the finals.

96
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,090
Maybe it was a mistake
to pair up with you.

97
00:05:53,790 --> 00:05:55,760
Please don't say that now.

98
00:05:57,820 --> 00:05:58,990
That's kind of harsh.

99
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:04,500
Hey, Junko...

100
00:06:05,770 --> 00:06:08,730
If we're off balance, then
how about if we include

101
00:06:08,730 --> 00:06:10,140
one more person?

102
00:06:14,570 --> 00:06:15,840
Her?

103
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:19,410
That's impossible.

104
00:06:20,810 --> 00:06:23,080
Not after I slapped
her the other day.

105
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:26,890
That's right. And doesn't
Yuka plan to do it alone?

106
00:06:27,590 --> 00:06:28,850
Is that right?

107
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:32,420
Can you seduce her?

108
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:36,730
I'm asking you if you have
the confidence to convince

109
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:38,400
her to join us.

110
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:41,770
Confidence... ?

111
00:06:42,730 --> 00:06:45,300
It's ok with me if
it's ok with you.

112
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:47,910
Go ahead, and convince her.

113
00:06:48,340 --> 00:06:51,110
You'd better apologize
to her properly, Junko.

114
00:06:53,710 --> 00:06:55,650
"Self-preservation
at all cost..."?

115
00:07:00,280 --> 00:07:02,590
Junko... Do you
have any savings?

116
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:05,460
I work part-time, so
I have a little bit.

117
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:06,560
Why?

118
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:10,430
The best way to a woman's
heart is food, isn't it?

119
00:07:12,660 --> 00:07:13,860
Yuka!

120
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:21,840
About the audition...

121
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:24,440
Won't you join
me and Junko?

122
00:07:24,910 --> 00:07:26,010
I'll pass...

123
00:07:26,010 --> 00:07:27,480
I'm going to
dance alone.

124
00:07:28,580 --> 00:07:30,810
Won't you think about it?

125
00:07:30,810 --> 00:07:32,950
We already have some
of the steps...

126
00:07:35,380 --> 00:07:36,690
Then show it to me.

127
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:56,410
That's not my style
of dancing...

128
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,740
In other words,
it won't work.

129
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:00,480
Then join us, and
make it work.

130
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,650
Besides, you and I don't
even get along, do we?

131
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,010
I don't want to end up
fighting with you like

132
00:08:05,010 --> 00:08:06,010
the last time.

133
00:08:06,010 --> 00:08:08,080
Can't you just
think about it?

134
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:10,290
This time, Junko said she's
willing to use a lot of

135
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:13,050
your ideas... Didn't you?

136
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,560
Can we just talk about it?

137
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,130
We can talk while eat.

138
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:21,330
It's Junko's treat!

139
00:08:21,860 --> 00:08:24,270
We could have steak, shabu
shabu or sushi.

140
00:08:25,530 --> 00:08:27,170
We could even have
pot stew...!

141
00:08:27,170 --> 00:08:29,300
We could go to a high-class
Japanese-style restaurant.

142
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,640
What do you like
to eat, Yuka?

143
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:38,580
I knew it wouldn't work
from the beginning.

144
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:41,220
For one thing, Yuka's father
owns dozens of restaurants,

145
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:44,750
so she's probably eaten
steak, shabu shabu or

146
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,620
Italian until she's
tired of them.

147
00:08:47,650 --> 00:08:49,490
That's true, but...

148
00:08:49,490 --> 00:08:52,690
That would catch my
attention right away.

149
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:56,830
Then maybe beef bowl or
ramen noodles might work.

150
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,600
Maybe it'll be so unusual,
it'll grab her attention.

151
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,170
But we'll finish eating
in five minutes.

152
00:09:01,170 --> 00:09:03,070
We won't be able to talk.

153
00:09:08,170 --> 00:09:09,940
Hitomi... How about "that"?

154
00:09:11,180 --> 00:09:13,280
You know... What we
had the other day.

155
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:16,250
Oh, "that"?

156
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,360
Yuka!

157
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:29,030
You're so persistent!
Don't bother me.

158
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:32,230
We don't have any lesson
tomorrow, do we?

159
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:33,630
So what about it?

160
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:35,800
Would you like to come to
Tsukishima and have "monja"?

161
00:09:36,370 --> 00:09:37,500
"Monja"?

162
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:38,900
That's right... "Monja.”

163
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:41,070
I've heard of it.

164
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:43,440
You fry it on an
iron griddle.

165
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:45,140
You mean "okonomiyaki"?

166
00:09:45,140 --> 00:09:46,440
No... it's different.

167
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:48,010
It's not quite as
well-done.

168
00:09:48,010 --> 00:09:49,580
The feel of it in your
mouth is something

169
00:09:49,580 --> 00:09:51,250
that's beyond comparison.
Isn't it?

170
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:55,920
I think I might like
to try it.

171
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:58,160
Maybe I'll go
with you.

172
00:10:13,570 --> 00:10:19,010
So, you're going to bring Yuka
and the others to eat "monja"?

173
00:10:19,610 --> 00:10:20,710
That's right.

174
00:10:20,710 --> 00:10:23,250
That's why I made reservations
at Makoto and Hiroshi's place.

175
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:26,450
Yuka's a really rich girl
so that's why I thought

176
00:10:26,450 --> 00:10:29,350
"monja" and a place like
this downtown area would

177
00:10:29,350 --> 00:10:31,150
be something new to her.

178
00:10:31,690 --> 00:10:33,120
I'm sure she'll love it.

179
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:35,990
In that case, after you
have "monja", why don't

180
00:10:35,990 --> 00:10:37,630
you bring her over here?

181
00:10:39,330 --> 00:10:41,400
So after you eat "monja",
you can take a walk

182
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:44,200
around, and work up an
appetite, then bring

183
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:47,470
her over here, and we can
have pot stew together.

184
00:10:48,910 --> 00:10:50,310
I'm all for pot stew!

185
00:10:50,310 --> 00:10:51,540
Me, too!

186
00:10:51,970 --> 00:10:53,010
Really?

187
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:54,940
Then I'll have to shop at Tsukiji tomorrow...

188
00:10:54,940 --> 00:10:57,250
Why do you put in "yosenabe"
pot stew anyway?

189
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:59,080
You should ask Yuzo
about that.

190
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:01,020
Knows a lot of cheap
and delicious places

191
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:02,120
