192
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,120
You're right.
I'm all for that.

193
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,090
Me, too!

194
00:11:04,090 --> 00:11:08,190
In that case, shall we invite
Yujiro and Ume, too?

195
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:12,260
I'm all for Yujiro
and Ume, too!

196
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:14,360
We'll do that then.

197
00:11:15,330 --> 00:11:16,830
I've had enough already!

198
00:11:17,330 --> 00:11:18,530
Act your age!

199
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:21,540
Is that Yuzo?

200
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:23,710
And Yujiro?

201
00:11:23,710 --> 00:11:25,170
What's going on anyway?

202
00:11:25,170 --> 00:11:26,470
What are they
fighting about?

203
00:11:26,470 --> 00:11:27,940
All you talk about is
Kamakura... Kamakura

204
00:11:27,940 --> 00:11:29,180
from morning until night.

205
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:30,810
Buying all these guidebooks.

206
00:11:30,810 --> 00:11:32,580
What are you going to
do with all of them?

207
00:11:32,580 --> 00:11:34,880
And who is this Gen Raicho?

208
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:38,390
It's Minamoto no Yoritomo!

Gen Raicho/Minamoto Yoritomo

209
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:40,420
He's the founder of the
Kamakura shogunate.

210
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:42,390
While we're on our date, that
topic might come up, so

211
00:11:42,390 --> 00:11:44,360
I have to study up on it.

212
00:11:44,930 --> 00:11:47,660
You're really having an
academic discussion here...

213
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:49,800
Talking about the Kamakura
shogunate and stuff like that.

214
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,170
Will you listen to this?

215
00:11:51,170 --> 00:11:53,730
All my idiot dad can think
about, is his date with Mari

216
00:11:53,730 --> 00:11:55,200
and he hardly does
any work anymore.

217
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,470
I was late just that
one morning, and

218
00:11:56,470 --> 00:11:58,040
that was because you
didn't wake me up.

219
00:11:58,040 --> 00:11:59,240
Why should I wake you up?

220
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,710
Ail you think about is your date.

221
00:12:00,710 --> 00:12:04,210
What? Are you against
my dating Mari?

222
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:06,610
What do you mean "date"?

223
00:12:06,610 --> 00:12:08,080
You're not a young kid.

224
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:11,150
My heart is as pure
as a young kid.

225
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:15,420
Have you looked at your
face lately? You look

226
00:12:15,420 --> 00:12:18,090
like a pigeon that's been
shot with a peashooter.

227
00:12:18,090 --> 00:12:19,260
Say that again!

228
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:21,430
That's enough, you two.

229
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:22,960
You're drawing a crowd.

230
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:25,930
You used to only talk about
our dried bonito flakes,

231
00:12:25,930 --> 00:12:27,870
or about our customers...
Now all you talk about

232
00:12:27,870 --> 00:12:32,540
from morning until night
is Kamakura... Kamakura!

233
00:12:32,540 --> 00:12:34,210
I can't take it anymore.

234
00:12:35,070 --> 00:12:36,110
Yuzo!

235
00:12:36,980 --> 00:12:38,080
Yuzo...?

236
00:12:38,740 --> 00:12:40,050
Did you hear that!

237
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:41,480
Lecturing his own
dad like that.

238
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,150
Shall I go, and
check on him?

239
00:12:43,150 --> 00:12:44,350
Go after him.

240
00:12:45,780 --> 00:12:47,050
Yujiro?

241
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:49,350
Aren't things going well
with your business?

242
00:12:49,350 --> 00:12:50,790
No... we're doing fine.

243
00:12:50,790 --> 00:12:54,190
But he was saying something
about your customers...

244
00:12:54,190 --> 00:12:56,430
It's about the future...

245
00:12:56,430 --> 00:12:58,660
Our customers are all
Japanese-style and

246
00:12:58,660 --> 00:13:02,870
old traditional style, high
class restaurants, so he was

247
00:13:02,870 --> 00:13:05,240
telling me to look at the
newer restaurants that

248
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:08,310
emphasize the taste of food.

249
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,910
I see... Yuzo's thinking
about the future in his

250
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:14,180
own way, isn't he?

251
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:17,980
Being the idiot
that he is...

252
00:13:19,420 --> 00:13:21,050
Sorry about the commotion.

253
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:22,450
Good night.

254
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:36,070
I've only seen him as man whose
mind is always on work,

255
00:13:36,070 --> 00:13:38,000
so it throws me off.

256
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:40,670
Seeing him getting so caught up
in something else like this.

257
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:41,870
It's a good thing...

258
00:13:41,870 --> 00:13:43,970
Age doesn't matter when it
comes to falling in love.

